<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1681] DocValues infinite loop caused by - a call to getMinValue | getMaxValue | getAverageValue</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1681</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.lucene.search.function.DocValues offers 3 public (optional) methods to access value statistics like min, max and average values of the internal values. A call to one of the methods will result in an infinite loop. The internal counter is not incremented. &lt;br/&gt;
I added a testcase, javadoc and a slightly different implementation to it. I guess this is not breaking any back compat. as a call to those methodes would have caused an infinite loop anyway.&lt;br/&gt;
I changed the return value of all of those methods to Float.NaN if the DocValues implementation does not contain any values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It might be considerable to fix this in 2.4.2 and 2.3.3&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
